  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rede D&apos;Or Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Founded in 1977, Rede DOr (Rede DOr or the Company) is a for-profit healthcare company that owns a network of46 image centers and laboratories for medical diagnostics and 16 hospitals (including three under construction at the time of appraisal) with over 1,500 beds total, in the states of Rio de Janeiro and Pernambuco.   

The company plans to invest over the next 4 to 5 years to support its organic growth strategy to expand existing facilities and build four new hospitals (three already under construction) to reach 2,700 beds total. The group also plans to acquire new hospitals.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will have significant development impact by: i) demonstrating best practices throughout the medical community; ii) increasing access to high quality medical care; and (iii) and acting as a catalyst for the rationalization of the private health sector in Brazil.</narrative>
  </description>
